      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in concours-level condition. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission. The mechanical integrity is superlative: the high-pressure VANOS system has been professionally overhauled, and the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced to ensure structural rigidity. Power is delivered via a factory M-Variable differential lock, providing exceptional traction and corner-exit telemetry. The chassis remains remarkably taut, with zero bushing deflection and a perfectly preserved suspension geometry. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the paint retains its factory depth and clarity. This is a turn-key, high-revving masterpiece for the collector who demands mechanical perfection and historical authenticity.",
